			<div class="span-one-third">
			    <h3>RDF Data access for</h3>
			    <ul>
                    <li><a href="/profile/">User profiles</a>
                        <ul><li><a href="/profile/cache/">cached data</a></li></ul>
                        </li>
                    <li><a href="#">Wall posts (soon)</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#">Messages (soon)</a></li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Authentication protocols</h3>
                <p><a href="http://webid.info"><img style="display: inline;" src="./img/webid.png" /> classic</a></p>
                <p><a href="http://www.w3.org/wiki/WebID/Authorization_Delegation"><img style="display: inline;" src="./img/webid.png" /> Delegated Authorization</a></p>
  			</div>
			<div class="span-one-third">
                <h3>Accepted request methods</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Read: GET, HEAD</li>
                    <li>Write: PUT, DELETE</li>
                    <li>Append: POST</li>
                </ul>
                <h3>Response content types</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>JSON: application/json</li>
                    <li>NTriples: */rdf+nt, */nt</li>
                    <li>RDF/XML: */rdf+xml</li>
                    <li>Turtle: */turtle, */rdf+n3, */n3</li>
                    <li>HTML: */html</li>
                </ul>
                <p>If no matching format is found, it defaults to turtle.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="span-one-third">
				<h3>Learn</h3>
				<p>The best way to learn how to use the MyProfile REST API is reading through the <a href="#">Documentation</a>.</p>
				<p>Another good resource is the <a href="#">Github Wiki</a>.</p>
