		<div class="row">
		    <p></p>
		    <h2>Here's a quick example of the API in action.</h2>
		    <p>The request:</p>
			<p><pre>HTTP/1.1 GET https://rest.example.com/profile/?webid=&lt;urlencoded WebID uri&gt;</pre><br/>
			With these extra header options:
			<pre>Accept: text/n3
On-Behalf-Of: https://my-profile.eu/people/deiu/card#me
            </pre>
			</p>
			<p>Will return*:</p>
			<p><pre><? echo htmlentities('<https://my-profile.eu/people/deiu/card#me>');?>
			
    a foaf:Person ;
    foaf:name "Andrei Vlad Sambra" ;
    foaf:givenName "Andrei Vlad" ;
    . . .
			</pre></p>
			<p>*The returned profile matches the access control policies specific to the user on whose behalf 
			the request is being made, and optionally the agent doing the request.</p>
